    "long_instructions": "### Live Coding\r\n\r\nA backing track is a sound that plays in the background during a live performance. It adds extra parts like a beat, chords, or effects to make the music sound fuller. While the backing track plays, the musician performs live and adds new parts on top of it.\r\n\r\n**Do this:** \r\n- Create a simple backing track with at least one drum and one bass sound played together. \r\n- Loop that backing track so it plays for at least 30 measures. ",
